{"tid":1402181,"cid":18,"subCid":0,"title":"ielts GT writing 求改(英文)","createTime":"2019-08-03T15:49:10.000Z","updateTime":"2019-08-04T07:41:20.000Z","uid":231530,"like":1,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":5,"replies":[{"pid":"48214b027df7634eaf5b1c9fc0826587a221a5df","tid":1402181,"uid":231530,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-08-03T15:49:10.000Z","msg":"Write a letter to an English-speaking friend. In your letter:<br />\n<br />\nexplain why you changed your previous job<br />\ndescribe your new job<br />\ntell him/her your other news<br />\n<br />\nDear Tom<br />\n<br />\nHope you are doing well, it&rsquo;s been so long since I&rsquo;ve heard from you. I&rsquo;m so glad to let you know that I have changed my job recently. Being an ambulance man, which save other&rsquo;s life, is always my dream. However it requires shift work and long working hours that made me suffering from insomnia, listening to my doctor's advice and considering the balance of life, I decided to change my job, which is to be a training officer.<br />\n<br />\nI got my new job offer, work as a first aid training officer, in St John Ambulance. It&rsquo;s duty is to train student who studies in secondary school as a qualified first aider. Working as a training officer not only gives me more satisfaction which training a group of first aider saves more lives, but it also gives me a work-life balance which I could work in office hours. Is that not cool?<br />\n<br />\nI would also like to inform you that my wife is having  a baby.  He&lsquo;ll be born on 18th July  2020, I bet you would definitely want to meet him as soon as possible, wouldn&rsquo;t you?<br />\n<br />\nI look forward to knowing what you are doing these days. Please write me back at your convenience.<br />\n<br />\nWarm wishes,<br />\n<br />\nChris"},{"pid":"b83cc925b5b9782fdc0c1e9037f80eec1d2a40d8","tid":1402181,"uid":231530,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-08-03T16:25:04.000Z","msg":